---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import HorizontalCard from "../components/HorizontalCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout sideBarActiveItemID="home">
  <div class="pb-12 mt-5">
    <div class="text-3xl py-3 font-bold">Welcome to my website!</div>

    <div class="py-2">
      <text class="text-lg">
        I am a Mechanical Engineer turned Computational Scientist, fascinated by solving complex problems that arise when humans decide to quantify nature.
      </text>
    </div>
    <div class="text-sm text-center text-base-content/60 py-3">
        Applied AI/ML · Probabilistic Modeling · Data Science · Computer Simulations · High Performance Computing
    </div>

    <div class="py-2 text-justify">
      <text class="text-sm">
        During my Postdoc, I collaborated with biologists to count millions of tiny cells inside terabyte-sized whole-brain scans, to understand the progression of neurodegenerative brain diseases;
partnered with neuroscientists to quantify the efficacy of novel drugs for Alzheimer's disease, based on the drug's dispersion in the brain;
and joined highly inter-disciplinary efforts to measure genetically induced cell toxicity, by analyzing millions of images acquired from genome-wide genetic perturbation (CRISPR) screens.
        As a PhD student, I was captivated by the inherent flexibility of erythrocytes and studied how their shape is optimized by nature, for maximum delivery of oxygen in arterioles.
I modeled the viscoelastic material properties of erythrocyte membranes and developed a hierarchical Bayesian model, able to predict their flow and reproduce experimental data and their uncertainty.
I simulated the flow of blood with sub-cellular resolution using mesoscopic, particle-based methods involving energy potentials, and derived dimensionless quantities fully describing the dynamics of the system.
I learned about fluid-structure interactions and modeled the interactions between erythrocytes, the surrounding fluid, and walls of microfluidics devices.
To save computational resources, I trained ML-based surrogate models to emulate the computationally expensive high-fidelity blood flow simulations.
        <br><br>
        A few highlights are showcased below — you can explore the full set on the <a href="/projects" class="link link-primary">Projects</a> page.
      </text>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-8">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:athena.eco@gmail.com" target="_blank">Get in touch</a>
      <a class="btn btn-outline ml-2" href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=EICX1aMAAAAJ" target="_blank">Google Scholar</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div>
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">Selected Research Projects</div>
  </div>

  <HorizontalCard
    title="Intracellular Protein Delivery to Neurons via Engineered Toxoplasma: 3D Brainwide Analysis"
    img="/avg_all_groups_hr.jpg"
    desc="An international collaboration developing a novel protein-based delivery system to the central nervous system using engineered Toxoplasma gondii secretion systems. 3D images of whole mouse-brain scans were used to quantify and map the brainwide spatial distribution of the delivered proteins, using light-sheet microscopy (mesoSPIM). Image processing was performed using a custom, in-house developed pipeline employing shared-memory parallelism, targeted for fast processing of large 3D image datasets."
    url="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41564-024-01750-6"
    badge="Nature Microbiology 2024"
    tags={['3D segmentation', 'HPC', 'Light-sheet microscopy', 'Machine Learning']}
  />
  <div class="divider my-0"></div>
  <HorizontalCard
    title="Drug Efficacy of Netoglitazone in Alzheimer's via Brainwide Microglia Segmentation & Mapping"
    img="/Microglia_hr.jpg"
    desc="Quantification of brainwide, region-specific effects of the antidiabetic drug netoglitazone in Alzheimer's mouse models, using quantitative whole-brain 3D histochemistry (Q3D) and light-sheet microscopy. Whole-brain 3D stacks processed with a custom pipeline for automated microglia segmentation, registration to the Allen Brain Atlas, and statistical mapping."
    url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0309489"
    badge="PLoS One 2025"
    tags={['3D image analysis', 'Drug efficacy', 'Machine Learning', 'Neurodegeneration']}
  />
  <div class="divider my-0"></div>
  <HorizontalCard
    title="Stress-Free State & Viscoelastic Properties of Red Blood Cells"
    img="/rbc-sfs_hr.jpg"
    desc="Can three simple experiments capture everything about a red blood cell? We show that resting shape, optical tweezers stretching, and relaxation dynamics are sufficient to infer all viscoelastic properties and the stress-free state via hierarchical Bayesian inference — yielding a transferable model that predicts cell dynamics in unseen shear flow conditions with unprecedented accuracy."
    url="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0006349523001728"
    badge="Biophysical Journal 2023"
    tags={['Bayesian inference', 'Hierarchical models', 'Membrane mechanics']}
  />

  <div class="divider my-0"></div>

  <div class="mt-8">
    <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/projects">View all projects →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-16">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">Open-Source Software</div>
  </div>

  <HorizontalCard
    title="img3D — 3D Volumetric Image Processing"
    desc="Python/C package for image processing of large, 3D (volumetric) image data. Supports raw file I/O, NRRD metadata, and parallel computation with OpenMP."
    url="https://github.com/aecon/img3D"
    target="_blank"
    badge="Python · C"
  />
  <div class="divider my-0"></div>
  <HorizontalCard
    title="AggreQuant — Automated High Content Screen Analysis"
    desc="Automated pipeline for segmentation and co-localization analysis of high content screening data, using deep learning (StarDist, Cellpose) for nuclei and cell segmentation."
    url="https://github.com/aecon/AggreQuant"
    target="_blank"
    badge="Python"
  />

  <div class="divider my-0"></div>

  <div class="mt-8">
    <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/software">View all tools →</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
